abstract_ssm: Joseph Magliacano (July 11, 1897-September 1997) was a labor activist in New Jersey and New York City. The collection contains correspondence and poetry, and notebooks, speeches and materials related to the United Furniture Workers of America (UFWA); it also includes photographs related to Joseph Magliacano's labor union activities (particularly the UFWA) as well as some personal and family photographs.
